{
    version     2.0;
    format      ascii;
    class       dictionary;
    location    "constant";
    object      gravitationalProperties;
}

dimensions      [0 1 -2 0 0 0 0];

g               dimensionedVector [0 1 -2 0 0 0 0] (0 -9.81 0);
```

This format places the dimension specification `[0 1 -2 0 0 0 0]` directly inside the `dimensionedVector` constructor where the `dimensionSet` parser can find it, satisfying the "expected a [`" requirement. The standalone `g` keyword outside serves as the entry name, and the `dimensionedVector` constructor receives the dimensions and value separately.

